<paragraph id="FD3F2DC91164E7477F8357967C66DF6A" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">Vielgestaltiges Berufkraut (keine Abbildung)</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</title>
<subSubSection id="E68021502B0F3EE1FD5316EA026FF856" pageId="null" pageNumber="539" type="description">
<paragraph id="B0FFF24EFAD3DD767DE1CB0F7A307365" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">
5-30 cm hoch. Stengel 1-3-, selten bis 6 
<normalizedToken id="EBFCC9E24648A73C1B52005F485862B0" originalValue="köpfig" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">koepfig</normalizedToken>
, meist 
<emphasis id="8798BA910DF84F36CF37647609E79C45" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">
<normalizedToken id="5FB5039159BF57E158E542D29B9757B9" originalValue="grün" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">gruen</normalizedToken>
</emphasis>
. 
<normalizedToken id="DBB13F30D62618D6E01423EDDFFFA4D5" originalValue="Grundständige" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">Grundstaendige</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="DB9A58A3247B01AC2D078F5447BD04A0" originalValue="Blätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">Blaetter</normalizedToken>
und 
<normalizedToken id="D6CB8FF27CA1667A6EC8BF7670518668" originalValue="Hüllblätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">Huellblaetter</normalizedToken>
wie 
<taxonomicName id="E31C44CF64C57EB34F436C336779AA8E" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Erigeron" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="null" pageNumber="539" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alpinus">
<emphasis id="570BBB8BD085E34B844DAF6F4228F52E" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">E. alpinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Nr. 9a), aber 
<emphasis id="DC8E9185EE32C55723D86D25BF768AFA" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">
die 
<normalizedToken id="157220B446354AA1C0EB96B9A1216AC9" originalValue="Blätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">Blaetter</normalizedToken>
nur am Rande behaart.
</emphasis>
<normalizedToken id="6578A42995C1F9D2BE18179F3C7ED6C4" originalValue="Zungenförmige" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">Zungenfoermige</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="118F89B9FB63E43A518B377987E2482B" originalValue="Blüten" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">Blueten</normalizedToken>
lila oder purpurrot. 
<emphasis id="A6E4FF23A10D47506DF0C44E91FED915" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">
Zwischen Zungen- und 
<normalizedToken id="87A2735D0CB0B47022BF6584E1A067B8" originalValue="Röhrenblüten" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">Roehrenblueten</normalizedToken>
keine 
<normalizedToken id="8E9876E0A59269830DB20EAFB5D7D703" originalValue="Fadenblüten" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">Fadenblueten</normalizedToken>
.
</emphasis>
- 
<normalizedToken id="F62F2027C9D76977267EA76D7F7CB8AA" originalValue="Blüte" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">Bluete</normalizedToken>
: Sommer und 
<normalizedToken id="124ADBAC05060FCA8504A3D436845CF1" originalValue="früher" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">frueher</normalizedToken>
Herbst.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F811591695724E97C19677385EB6BCBA" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">
<emphasis id="E1C2197873CC82C8360F8145A897F2C2" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">Zytologische Angaben. 2n</emphasis>
= 
<emphasis id="F7F3FCB47D55CE76B5CE53AF1CB10109" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">18:</emphasis>
Material unbekannter Herkunft (Sakai aus Darlington und Wylie 1955), aus den Alpen (Reese 1953). Matsura und Suto (aus Darlington und Wylie 1955) 
<normalizedToken id="2CF70E80366E359249DBF507A8856FC1" originalValue="zählten" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">zaehlten</normalizedToken>
<emphasis id="0247BD8FD8754D5D1DC0135CB5CBEB55" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">2n</emphasis>
= 
<emphasis id="631C99D803392B5310E3EFCC2DCC6758" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">36.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3AAAB115776C64814F652A28EC08746D" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">
<emphasis id="0F9CA2D7B4E25A7CECDA7A412C666782" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">Standort.</emphasis>
Subalpin und alpin, selten montan. Kalkfelsen, seltener auch im Kalkschutt. 
<emphasis id="B9C28FD93488C759BA55D29AF299A8E5" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">Potentillo-Hieracietum humilis</emphasis>
Br.-Bl. 1933, seltener im 
<emphasis id="3A161A6E3B4B767578A55E80C197020C" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">Caricetum firmae</emphasis>
Br.-Bl. 1926.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D88CC834F07A5BE816BA4BC33B2B091B" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">
<emphasis id="EE45375F774BC8D5E38B56AB690CD98B" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">Verbreitung. Mittel</emphasis>
- 
<emphasis id="2E22C45148894F1F79FC9CC38210216E" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">
und 
<normalizedToken id="D0D86E53EE9C0317B49751A7F74B2B29" originalValue="südeuropäische" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">suedeuropaeische</normalizedToken>
Gebirgspflanze:
</emphasis>
<normalizedToken id="C4ED0496936B2E30261A8EF67641F3C8" originalValue="Pyrenäen" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">Pyrenaeen</normalizedToken>
, Jura, Alpen (Alpes Maritimes bis Wiener Schneeberg), Apennin, Karpaten, Gebirge der Balkanhalbinsel. - Im Gebiet: Alpen und 
<normalizedToken id="E64BE6E084D231D96B2C9EFD567C8E21" originalValue="südlicher" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">suedlicher</normalizedToken>
Jura (
<normalizedToken id="4C55EF7CF1A14DF428BBCFCE9A270B69" originalValue="nordostwärts" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">nordostwaerts</normalizedToken>
bis Creux du Van), nicht 
<normalizedToken id="F0A56E67A6673AA2B1D212DB4282E211" originalValue="häufig" pageId="null" pageNumber="539">haeufig</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
